{{Quote|Nym. All of this here is his stronghold.|[[Finn Darktrin]]|<ref name="TRoD">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: The Ruins of Dantooine]]''</ref>}}
'''Nym's Stronghold''' was the largest city and sole planetary [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] on the planet [[Lok/Legends|Lok]]. It was built prior to the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] around the [[Nym's Base|base]] used by [[Nym/Legends|Nym]] and his [[Lok Revenants/Legends|pirates]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

==Description==
{{Quote|There's only one starport on Lok that can handle that ship of yours... So will it be Nym's Stronghold for you then?|A [[Lok Station]] operator|<ref name="SWG:JtL">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: Jump to Lightspeed]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Nym_Stronghold_2.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Nym's Stronghold, as seen from the starport.]]
Nym's Stronghold was located on the desert planet [[Lok/Legends|Lok]], in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]. The city was located on the banks of the [[Grendin River]] and bordered the cliffs where [[Nym/Legends|Nym]] established his [[Nym's Base|base]] before the [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|Invasion of Naboo]]. Considered as a stronghold itself, the city was surrounded by tall walls. It was controlled by the [[Lok Revenants/Legends|Lok Revenants]] and was patrolled by Nym's guards<ref name="SWG" /> and by trained [[kusak]]s.<ref name="SWG:CftK">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=collection|Caring for the Kusaks}}</ref>

A bridge connected the main part of the city to a landing platform, on the other shore of the Grendin River.<ref name="SWG" /> Nym's Stronghold was the only [[Spaceport/Legends|starport]] in the [[Karthakk system]].<ref name="AtR">{{SonyCite|url=players/content.vm?id=66934&resource=features|text=Aiding the Rebellion}}</ref> To access this starport, starships needed to be cleared for landing at the [[Lok Station|Lok Space Station]] orbiting the planet.<ref name="SCKS">{{SonyCite|url=en_US/players/content.vm?id=66849&resource=features|text=Star Chart: Karthakk System}}</ref> In any case, Nym's Stronghold was a haven for outlaws, pirates and [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]].<ref name="AtR" />

==History==
{{Quote|So where do we find Nym?|[[Dusque Mistflier]]|<ref name="TRoD" />}}
[[File:Nym_guards.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Nym's guards patrolling the city.]]
Nym's Stronghold was built sometime after the Lok Revenants [[Battle of Lok (22 BBY)|reclaimed]] their old base from the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] at the beginning of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="JS" /> By the time of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], Nym had become the unique ruler of Lok and the city could be considered ''de facto'' as his capital.<ref name="Insider65">{{InsiderCite|65|Who's Who in Star Wars Galaxies|Who's Who in ''Star Wars'' Galaxies}}</ref> Nevertheless, Nym remained a pirate and was quite reluctant to deal with daily matters of his city. After the Battle of Yavin, a mob of disgruntled townspeople protested near Nym's fortress against the shortage of drinkable water in the city. This situation forced Nym to send his henchmen fix the water treatment facility.<ref name="SWG:TPAR" /> Around the same time, another Revenant, [[Ran Machado]], was tasked by Nym to pull up some of the unintended foliage in the Stronghold.<ref name="SWG:WWFR">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Weed Whacker Foliage Requisition|Lok}}</ref>

Nym's Stronghold was the starting point of the [[Lok Marathon]] [[Swoop racing|swoop race]].<ref name="SWG:LM">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=other}}Swoop race track: "Lok Marathon" on Lok</ref> After the Battle of Yavin, the champion [[Kimmi Chyler]] used to travel to the city to participate to the race. During one such race, a firefight erupted between the smuggler [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]] and [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|ISB]] [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Jeffren Brek]].<ref name="TSS">{{SWGTCG|set=The Shadow Syndicate|scenario=Light Side and Dark Side scenario campaigns}}</ref>

[[File:Nym_Keep.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Nym's Keep]]
After the Battle of Yavin, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] traveled to the Stronghold. As Nym was sympathetic towards the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], they wished to convince him to support actively the Rebellion.<ref name="SWG:MPwN">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=faction|Rebel|Making Peace with Nym|Lok}}</ref> [[Dusque Mistflier]] and [[Finn Darktrin]] also visited the city in [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]] and met Nym on his fortress.<ref name="TRoD" />

The same year, Nym's Stronghold held a large anniversary celebration known as [[Nym's Anniversary Bash]].<ref name="SWAB">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=67239&month=052007|text=Friday Feature – Star Wars Anniversary Bash}}</ref>

